title: tickWindows mutates profiles without bumping dataEpoch
updated_at: "2026-07-15T04:40:40Z"
---
## Problem
`tickWindows` mutates profile objects via shallow `profiles.slice()` without bumping `dataEpoch`. Main listens to `onProfilesChanged`, which usually fires on array reassignment, but ExpandedView’s model expression also keys off `dataEpoch`. Relying on both paths is fragile if a future change mutates in place without reassigning `profiles`.

## Location
contents/ui/ProfileController.qml:629-647

## Suggested fix
Bump `dataEpoch` (throttled) on tick, or ensure a consistent single notification path for UI sync.

## Source
Review ff0a2eec Issue 18 (suggestion)